reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good product!
reviews.reviewText: I have been using this Apple charger for my Mac Book Pro for a while now and I can't say enough good things about it! It charges my device quickly and efficiently, without any hiccups or interruptions. Plus, the charging cord is long enough to give me the flexibility to use my device comfortably while it's charging. The charger seems durable and well-made. Overall, I'm extremely satisfied with my purchase and would highly recommend this charger to any Mac Book Pro users out there. It's worth every penny!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great travel charger
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as a travel alternative charger for my ASUS ProArt Studiobook 16, as well as for my Canon R6 Mark II. It works well for both of them and charges the devices really quickly. Not many chargers work with Canon R6 Mark II, but this one works well. The original ASUS charger adapter is 240W, vs. this one that is 118W, so it will be understandably slower than the ASUS one, and it gets a bit hot, but if you want to save space for traveling and charge your gaming laptop, it is a great option. When compared to the original ASUS charger, this one is much lighter (200 g vs 660 g) and twice smaller and less bulkier considering cables, so it is great for traveling.

The product is not so bad overall however the outlet adapter of the charger makes sparks when I plug it in the outlet and the charger does not charge. It’s a fire hazard.Had to change the adapter part for another one.
